Raheem Sterling and Daniel Sturridge unveiled Liverpool's new home kit at Anfield on Friday . 
  The 2015/16 strip is US sports brand New Balance's first for the club . 
  New Balance struck a record-breaking £300million four-year kit deal with Liverpool . 
  Sterling rejected a £100,000-a-week contract with the club last week . 
  Liverpool face Aston Villa in the FA Cup semi-final at Wembley on Sunday . 
  Simon Mignolet, Martin Skrtel and Sterling unveiled the kit to fans . 
 